  "details": "Cockpit enables users to administer GNU/Linux servers using a web browser. It offers network configuration, log inspection, diagnostic reports, SELinux troubleshooting, interactive command-line sessions, and more.  \n\nSecurity Fix(es):  \n\n  * cockpit: Cockpit: Arbitrary command execution via crafted links in system logs UI (CVE-2026-4802)\n\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n",
